The paper deals with the complexity analysis of a reconfiguration problem for integer linear systems, which involves changing one variable at a time while maintaining feasibility. This problem is related to computational complexity, algorithms, and discrete mathematics, which are all covered by the arXiv categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely, as the paper focuses on the complexity analysis of a computational problem. cs.DM and cs.LO are also relevant, as the paper deals with integer linear systems and their properties. cs.AI is less likely, but still possible, as the paper may have implications for optimization and decision-making problems.
